Story Title: As a developer, I want to refine filtering, pagination, and sorting to decrease response time so that end-users can have a more rewarding experience.
As a developer, I want to refine our technical documentation so that anyone interested in learning about the way our site was developed can easily understand the tools and procceses used.
As a developer, I want to add more comments to our codebase, so that when I revisit it in a couple weeks I don't hate myself becuase I can't understand what's happening.
As a developer, I want to refactor the front-end code to remove duplicate into reusable functionality to reduce the size of the JS being deployed and increase the sites speed.
As a front-end developer, I want to use Selenium to create unit tests so that I can ensure the site displays to the user as anticipated.
As a developer, I want to store media within our backend so that we can speed up response time by eliminating unnecessary external queries.
As a developer, I want to refactor the API routes to allow for more robust filtering so that the front-end can implement more efficient filtering.
As a developer, I want to implement caching in the back-end so that we can provide a richer user experience.
As a developer, I want to create a visualization by using another teams API so that we can meet the requirements for this project.
As a developer, I want to refine the documentation for the API so that other developers can easily consume our API to make interesting vizualizations.
As a developer, I want to be able to see solid documentation for the API, so that I can use your API without struggling to understand it.
As a user, I want to be able to search your website for something specific,  so that I can easily find what I'm looking for.
As a developer, I want to be able to collect information from your API, so that I can build my own awesome website.
As a socialite, I want to be able to easily find the social media links for breweries I am interested in so that I can stay up to date.
As a beer enthusiast, I want to be able to view limited beers per page, so that I am not overwhelmed by the number of beers on a single page.
As a user, I want to be able to filter beers by specific attributes, so that I can find only the beers that interest me.
As a user, I want to be able to view your website from multiple devices, so that I can get my beer info on the fly.
As a user, I want to be able to visit your site from the browser of my choice, so that I don't have to get a new browser.
As a user, I want to view well-formatted review comments, so that I can easily read them.
As a developer, I want solid documentation about your API so that I can easily understand how to consume your RESTful API
As a frugal person, I want to be able to easily browse beers by ABV, so that I can get the best bang for my buck.
As a developer, I want to be able to query API endpoints to collect beer data from the brewtiful.world API
As a dark beer lover, I want to be able to find new stouts and porters, so that I can expand my beer horizons.
As a sports fan, I want to easily find reviews on local breweries and beers, so that I can stock my fridge with the best stuff for game day.
As a beer enthusiast, I want to find top-rated breweries, so that I can go try new beers from good breweries.
As a traveler, I want to be able to find the best beers in places I travel to, so that I can experience local brews.
As a curious person, I want an easy way to learn about different styles of beer, so that I can better understand the profile of new beers I try.
As a student, I want to be able to read many reviews on beers and breweries, so that I can easily find the best option for drinking away my sorrows after a SWE test.
As a bar owner, I want to easily view many breweries, so that I can learn about great places to get beer for stocking my bar.
As a beer enthusiast, I want to see many beers listed on the beer page, so that I can easily access and learn about many different beers.
